public class NCLMapping<T extends NCLElement,En extends NCLNode,Ei extends NCLInterface>
extends NCLElementPrototype<T>
implements NCLElement<T>

Class that represents a mapping element. This element represents a mapping from a switchPort element to a switch inner node or node interface point.
This element defines the attributes:

  • component - node mapped by the mapping element. This attribute is required.
  • interface - node interface point mapped by the mapping element. This attribute is optional.

setComponent

public void setComponent(En component)
                  throws XMLException
Sets the node mapped by the mapping element. This attribute is required and can not be set to null.
The node referred must be a node defined in the switch parent of the switch port that has this mapping element.

Parameters:
component - element representing a reference to a node element.
Throws:
XMLException - if the node is null or any error occur while creating the reference to the node.

setInterface

public void setInterface(Ei interfac)
                  throws XMLException
Sets the node interface point mapped by the mapping element. This attribute is optional. Set the interface to null to erase a interface already defined.
The interface referred must be a interface point of the node referred by the component attribute.

interfac - element representing a reference to a interface element or null to erase a interface already defined.
